# Git Commit Configuration

When making git commits, agents must use the following identity:

- **Name**: "PuzzleSolverAgent"
- **Email**: "puzzle-solver-agent@aoc.com"

Configure git before committing:
```bash
git config user.name "PuzzleSolverAgent"
git config user.email "puzzle-solver-agent@aoc.com"
```

Or use the `--author` flag in commit commands:
```bash
git commit --author="PuzzleSolverAgent <puzzle-solver-agent@aoc.com>" -m "commit message"
```

